  "contentHtml": "\n    \n    \n                                    \n                                                                                    <ul>\n                                                                                                                                                    <li><a href=\"/agency/88675387/ET-Bureau\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ET Bureau</a></li>\n                                                                                            </ul>\n                                                                                <ul>\n                                                                                            <li>Published On Apr 17, 2026 at 07:59 AM IST</li>\n                                                                                                                                </ul>\n                                    \n                                \n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure>Germany-based medtech firm <a href=\"/tag/siemens+healthineers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Siemens Healthineers</a> is looking to collaborate with the <a href=\"/tag/karnataka+government\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Karnataka government</a> to support upcoming <a href=\"/tag/centres+of+excellence\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">centres of excellence</a> in <a href=\"/tag/lifesciences\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">lifesciences</a>, <a href=\"/tag/healthtech\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">healthtech</a> and medical products, IT/BT minister Priyank Kharge said on Thursday.Kharge met the leadership team of <a href=\"/tag/siemens\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Siemens</a> Healthineers in Bengaluru to discuss opportunities around skilling, joint incubation and partnerships aligned with the state’s deeptech push, he wrote on X.<!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->“We discussed opportunities to collaborate on skilling, joint incubation and our upcoming <a href=\"/tag/centres+of+excellence\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">centres of excellence</a> in <a href=\"/tag/lifesciences\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">lifesciences</a>, <a href=\"/tag/healthtech\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">healthtech</a> and medical products,” the minister said in the post. “We also explored how they can engage more closely with Karnataka’s startup ecosystem under our Deeptech Decade initiatives.”\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        He added that it is encouraging to see global companies deepen their presence in the state, backed by the state's strong talent base and innovation ecosystem.<!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><a href=\"/tag/siemens\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Siemens</a> Healthineers, which counts Bengaluru among its four global innovation hubs, operates a global capability centre (GCC) in the city focused on areas such as <a href=\"/tag/data+analytics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">data analytics</a>, <a href=\"/tag/artificial+intelligence\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">artificial intelligence</a> and immersive technologies.The collaboration comes amid the company actively partners with <a href=\"/tag/deeptech+startups\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">deeptech startups</a> in India, particularly in the healthcare sector.<!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->During the meeting, the company shared updates on its upcoming <a href=\"/tag/bengaluru+campus\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Bengaluru campus</a>, which will integrate research and development, manufacturing and training functions, Kharge said.The city already hosts a significant share of Siemens Healthineers’ global R&amp;D and engineering talent, reinforcing its role as a key hub for the company, he added.                    \n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                    \n\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/88675387/ET-Bureau\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ET Bureau</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> Updated On Apr 17, 2026 at 07:59 AM IST</li> -->\n                                    <li>Published On Apr 17, 2026 at 07:59 AM IST</li>\n                                    <!-- <li class=\"desktop-view\">1 min read</li> -->\n                                </ul>\n                            \n                                        \n\n                    \n\n                    <!-- Comment Section -->\n                                            \n                                        <!-- Comment Section -->\n\n                    \n                      \n    \n            <p>\n                </p><h2>Join the community of 2M+ industry professionals. </h2>   \n                <h3>Subscribe to Newsletter to get latest insights &amp; analysis in your inbox.</h3>\n            <p></p>\n\n            <!-- <figure class=\"top-newsletter-subs__icon-nl\" role=\"presentation\" aria-label=\"Newsletter icon\">\n                <img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://st.etb2bimg.com/Themes/Release/theme4/images/icons/icon-newsletter.svg\" alt=\"Newsletter icon\" width=\"55\" height=\"55\">\n            </figure> -->\n        \n            \n                \